      <body>
         <entry xml:id="delatoria-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#daiteqe-dlgenr"
                next="#dimosia-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">דילטוריא</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">dylṭwryʾ</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">delaṭoriaʾ</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">f.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">דילטוריה</orth>
                  <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">dylṭwryh</orth>
                  <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">delaṭoriah</pron>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Vat1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" opt="false">דילטוריא</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Ox2 V" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" opt="false">דלטוריא</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Ox1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" opt="false">דילטורא</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="K" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" opt="false">דילוטריה</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Vat2" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" opt="false">דילאטרייא</orth>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="delatoria-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false">law</usg>
               <usg type="socioCultural" norm="borrowing" opt="false">cultural borrowing</usg>
               <usg type="normativity" opt="false">standard</usg>
               <usg type="meaningType" opt="false">lit.</usg>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>accusation</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>slander</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Medieval Greek</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>δηλατορία</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="la">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Latin</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>dēlātūra</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>
                     ר' יהושע דסכנין בשם ר' לוי התחיל אומר דילטוריה לבוראו [Ox 1 Ox 2 Vat 1 V על בוראו]
         </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">19,4</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 172: 10</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                        R. Yehoshuaʿ of Sikhnin said in R. Lewi’s name: He [the serpent] began speaking slander of his Creator… (Freedman / Simon I 150)
            </bibl>
                  </cit>
                  <note anchored="true">=
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 27 [8d: 36]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">דלטוריא</term>);
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">MTeh 1,9 [10]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">לשון הרע</term>);
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Tan Meṣoraʿ 2 [23]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">לה"ר</term>);
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">TanB Meṣoraʿ 7</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">לשון הרע</term>);
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">ExR 3,12</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">לשון הרע</term>);
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">DtnR Shofeṭim 5,10</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">לשון הרע</term>) [several similar passages, all with <term xml:lang="jpa">לשון הרע</term>]
         </note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym type="borrowing" opt="false">
               <lbl opt="false">source language</lbl>
               <lang opt="false">Latin (via Greek)</lang>
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="la">
                  <xr type="related" opt="false">
                     <lbl opt="false">Cf. Lewis / Scott</lbl>
                     <ref target="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/morph?l=d%C4%93l%C4%81t%C5%ABra&amp;la=la&amp;can=d%C4%93l%C4%81t%C5%ABra0"
                          type="entry">dēlātūra</ref>
                  </xr>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
               For Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">δηλατορία</term> cf. 
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Soph. 354b</bibl>,
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">LBG I 351b</bibl>. This form, used only in Aramaic, is attested also by
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">yBer 1,2 [7: 31]</bibl>;
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">yShab 1,2 [368: 47]</bibl>;
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">CantR 1,6</bibl> (
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">yPea 1,1 [83: 37]</bibl> is corr. <term xml:lang="jpa">דילטורין</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">dylṭwryn</term>, cf. ibid. 83:27). According to
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Krauss, LW II 204a</bibl>: Lat. delatura (cf. the reading of Ox 1 and
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">PesR 33 [150b: 28]</bibl>) with parasitic vowel (cf.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Krauss, LW I 132</bibl>); this form is attested already by Targum Yonatan for Gen 3,4.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Levy I 408a</bibl>: Lat. delatoria. Cf. also
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Jastrow I 299a</bibl>. For <term xml:lang="jpa">דילטור</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">dylṭwr</term>
               <term xml:lang="rabbinic">delaṭor</term>, pl. <term xml:lang="jpa">דלטורין</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">dlṭwryn</term>
               <term xml:lang="rabbinic">delaṭorin</term>, “informer, sycophant”, not attested in GenR, cf.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">AC III 68b-69a</bibl>;
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Levy I 407b</bibl>;
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Krauss, LW II 203b-204a</bibl>;
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Jastrow I 299b</bibl>.
   </note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <title>Sokoloff, DJPA</title>
                  <citedRange>140b</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
